str2: To will, wish, desire, be willing, intend, design.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Humility, lowliness of mind, modesty. From a compound of tapeinos and the base of phren; humiliation of mind, i.e. Modesty.
From a derivative of threskos; ceremonial observance.
From aggello; a messenger; especially an 'angel'; by implication, a pastor.

str2: From kata and brabeuo; to award the price against, i.e. to defraud.

str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

str2: From en and a presumed derivative of the base of basis; equivalent to embaino; to intrude on.

str2: Properly, to stare at, i.e. to discern clearly; by extension, to attend to; by Hebraism, to experience; passively, to appear.

str2: From phusis in the primary sense of blowing; to inflate, i.e. make proud.
Without a cause, purpose; purposelessly, in vain, for nothing. Probably from eiko; idly, i.e. Without reason.
A primary preposition; under, i.e. of place, or with verbs; of place (underneath) or where (below) or time (when).

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Flesh, body, human nature, materiality; kindred.
Probably from the base of ginosko; the intellect, i.e. Mind; by implication, meaning.
